caption: Gotta appreciate a spot that has actually creative, good tasting options for vegetarian rolls. The appetizers are all 💯 too.

I used to love sticky rice. I order via Postmates when I picked up my order I notice my order was incorrect I tried to get it fix but after talking to the manager (Matt) omg that man is the worst.This will definitely be my last time ordering from them the service has gone downhill from my first visit.

My order was incorrect and the food quality has just gone insanely downhill. I don't know what happened but this will be my last visit to Sticky Rice. And the prices have been inflated beyond the quality.  And it's been 30 minutes and I am still on hold....

Unfortunately it is sad to say that this company has lost greart business from me. I ordered through Door dash today, ordering chicken sesame and I fount hair weaved in my food. This is a first from this company and I've been a long time consumer for 13 years. I will not be returning to this establishment. This is disgusting.
Best sushi in town..rest of the stuff Is ok
Amazing sushi, poke bowl, and miso soup! I got takeout and the guy even handed it to us at the front door. Everything was delicious.
Great staff, cool vibe! Serving size to price ratio makes it hard to return. The Mango and sticky rice was extremely disappointing! Might have been a bad end of the night experience.

So I understand that COVID has caused businesses to change strategies on the fly but this was not well planned. Getting the food was the sketchiest I have experienced and the food was mediocre. We decided to order from sticky rice yesterday at a rec from a friend. We have never ordered before but my husband knew it was on h st. We made a trip out of it and tucked our two month old in the car seat and I plugged in the address it gave me when making the order. I am not well versed with that area so when it said fenwick st as the address, I made nothing of it until my husband asked where we were going when he saw it wasn't h st. When we got there it was a literal alley with people milling about. The address was the door of a clearly closed run down auto shop. I tried calling their number from the website to no response. My husband did not want to go into a sketchy alley so he drove us to the h st location. The place looked closed and a sign said they were temporarily closed with no other information. I tried calling the number again to no response and looked at their fb and insta sites for any updates to no success. My husband called his friend who said they ordered from the h st location six days ago so that was very odd. I looked at google and Yelp reviews with no success. He thought I might have ordered from a scam site. Finally we decided to go back to the sketchy alley at Fenwick and saw some people walking out with paper bags. So my husband went into the alley and found nothing except people wandering about and a man harassing him saying he has been looking for him since the morning. He started to head back to the car when he saw a small sign tucked in at the corner of the alley saying sticky rice with a different number from the website. He called that number and at first they said they didn't have the order. Suddenly they then said they found the order and they said to wait there. A guy came out of a garage that was half open and gave him the brown bag. The food itself was mediocre but not worth the price. The miso soup was $6 for barely a cup of broth! The chicken that my husband got had no taste. The hash browns were soggy. The sushi tasted like something I could get from my work cafeteria. Once again I understand COVID can cause crazy changes but this was not well done at all. And the baby looked at us like we were the crazy ones by the time we were done with the adventure.
I really miss going to this place pre-COVID. Really great drinks (Kofi made ours) and the food was good too. I loved their decor and the karaoke night were fun.
Sushi was incredibly stale. I've had tastier grocery store sushi than what I got last night. Would definitely not order from here again.

I used to love this place, but it seems like the pandemic has really taken a toll on their operation. The attitude I have received by their team when I've gone to pick up takeout was really off-putting.  I couldnt help but think the last few times of ordering : "is this really worth the price?"
Wow 23 different vegan rolls. Cool quirky atmosphere, like the one in Baltimore. Good location. Order online; they don’t take phone orders.

I order sticky rice via uber eats, when I received the food I noticed two items were left out of the order. I called sticky rice regarding this and was placed on hold for an hour. It was late at that point so I hung up and called the next day to inform the AGM of my experience. He said he would look into this and get back to me within the hour. It was 3 hours later and I had to reach out. I was given a credit for the issue. My biggest concern is the lack of following through on their word, which happened twice. I work in hospitality myself and understand mistakes happen but the way you recover from them makes the differences. In this case, I was completely let down with how this recovery situation went.  Hope they use this as  learning situation for the future.

Has gone downhill a little. Ordered sushi the other night. Rolls have very big pieces but mostly rice and all frills, not much actual fish. Very small pieces of fish.  This was the case for most rolls that we ordered.  Also the flavors were very bland. Not good value for money.  Sushi Hachi on 8th St has better actual sushi.
Santa Fe roll is to die for
Sushi with fish was inedible (tasted like freezer burn) rice dishes were good and the vegetarian sushi was fine.

I ordered their poke bowl off of GrubHub and it was one of the most disappointing experiences. The "bowl" was more like a tiny little cup and the ingredients all tasted stale. It was such a waste of money I actually feel scammed. Their delivery on the apps is called Hello Poke. Avoid and don't make the mistake I did.
They're a little pricey but, so WROTH IT!!! Best Sushi in DC period!

Food is bland, and the flavor combinations are strange. We ordered a platter and nearly every roll came with cream cheese. A bit off putting considering the online portal described the platter as the  "classics"

I loved Sticky Rice. I had been eating from them since I moved to DC almost 5 years ago. That said, the last time I ordered food from them I got food poisoning. I think it was the schezan shrimp, and that the shrimp was not fully cooked or something. Maybe the tots had been sitting out too long. Not sure. I just know it was from them, because I hadn’t really eaten much all day for it to be anything else. I know it couldn’t have been the fully boiled and recently bought Whole Foods eggs I had for breakfast.  Because I like the place, I decided to call and let them know what happened. The manager I spoke to just said “okay”. Didn’t ask what I ordered, or around what time I ordered to try and even pretend like he cared. I was surprised at his lack of concern.  Therefore, I’ll never order from them again. It was a sad day indeed.

I am vegetarian and miss sushi very much! Sticky Rice has great options available for vegetarians who love sushi, and are looking for creative options instead of a boring cucumber or avocado are a mainstream sushi place. Great job Sticky Rice. I will be returning!
DO NOT order pickup from this place. The food is never ready, and I had to wait 20 mins for my food with an Uber waiting. I almost left it there!
Expensive, but good

I’m very disappointed to share this as I have been trying to support local restaurants during this difficult time. But I won’t be back anytime soon.

My order today was not good at all.  The pot stickers were hard and the beef dish was not tasty and the rice noodles was hard and very undercook.  I will not try this place again.  No taste and I spent $40 on something that I didn't enjoy.

Stay away. Don't waste your time.  We used to visit often when the parents came to town. We liked it well enough—local spot with no frills sushi and other items. We could even mix it up with wings or a bowl of tots. Not bad!  But quality has collapsed and we will not be going back.  Simply put, the service is awful. The food quality has declined. And the restaurant's interior just feels dingy and ignored. Hell, the last time we visited the upstairs bathroom light didn't work.  The final straw was tonight when we ordered take out through a delivery service. We ordered four items including a couple big ticket sushi dishes. What arrived was barely enough food for one, including a missing salad and a "soup" that was in a half container that wouldn't fit a bowl.  Take our critiques for what they are worth. However, we are not picky eaters, and having worked in service my wife and I both get it when servers are rushed or don't have the resources they need.  However, from my experience, this restaurant has such an indifference toward its customer experience that is can only be described as disdain. There is zero reason you should spend a dime at this place.

try the Godzilla roll 🥰 I was kept waiting quite a bit, and I ended up getting a spicy tuna instead of a regular, but they had a new trainee and they definitely made it worth my while with some treats on the house.

If you're looking for a unique restaurant with good service check out Sticky Rice. They serve up both original & classic styles of sushi as well as other dishes. Murals & paintings by local artists are throughout the restaurant. If karaoke is your thing then that's 1 more reason to head there. Sing Sing Karaoke Bar is on the 2nd floor. Ask about the karaoke league. This place should be on Food Network!

Takeout used to be high end. The vibe is still awesome 👌 but the quality has gone down for the price. Flavors are unique and good but the portions are smaller and the presentation cheap. My food juiced all over the bag.
Amazing affordable food! Great customer service too!

Don't waste your time at Sticky Rice. My wife and I wanted sushi and we had been to sticky rice before and liked it but never again. We sat on the 2nd floor that had a number of flies buzzing around the tables. We had to get our own plates and utensils after repeatedly asking for them. Our server disappeared for some time and did not put our entire order in. It took him 15 minutes to bring us the wrong beer and another 20 after that to bring us a new one. We finally received our entire order after placing it again with the hostess. She was the only bright spot of a rather dismal meal. She was busing tables, running to the kitchen and gave us our bill because our server disappeared once again. Unfortunately, the bill was incorrect because our server decided to charge us for the free beers he gave us for the long wait.  The server finally came back and apologized and had the nerve to say, " You have been here before so I am sure we will see you again." He couldn't be more wrong. There are a ton of options in DC with better food and service. I will never be back. If I were you I would avoid Sticky Rice and spend your hard earned money elsewhere.

Ordered from uber eats for and they didn't give me any soy sauce for my sushi. It totally threw off my lunch, especially how expensive it all was. My ribs were also cold, but at least I could fix that issue. The rolls were passing.
Great graduation party for friends daughter graduating from Gallaudet. Private room, karaoke and excellent food. Outstanding service. Thanks for making the party a success!

Do not go to this restaurant if you're looking for authentic sushi. They don't make good rolls nor do they use fresh ingredients. Also, the place is short staffed and the bar tenders are over worked. I would suggest another restaurant.

Good food but small portions for the price you pay. Had to wait 20 minutes for a table and ended up getting seated at the bar anyways where it was first come first serve.

The kitchen is chaotic - food not ordered was cooked, food ordered was brought to the wrong table, and of course it takes forever to get what you ordered and your check. I will not come back. Oh by the way, it has nothing to do with sticky rice whatsoever.

This is one of the best places in DC for creative and affordable food. I love their unique take on sushi and different rice bowls. The tater tots with yum yum sauce are virtually like crack. I have taken countless people here and the food never fails. I always have great service, an H street staple.

Always pleased with Sticky Rice. The Sticky Balls (pictured) are devine, love the caviar they chose for the topping. Singapore Noodles are a must. Jalapeno margarita was super refreshing. Lychee-tini is an acquired taste, made fun with that chunk of lychee.

Nice vibe, great food and service.  A little pricey,  but its DC, so you mustn't expect it to be cheap.  However,  it's worth the visit.  Be sure to call ahead for reservations,  because this place is popular.

Nick our waiter was great.

We had to wait 25 minutes for a table and it did seem like other people were being seated before us, but as soon as we were seated we were given outstanding service by a guy in really cool shoes (I'm sorry I'm forgetting his name - he deserves credit!) We never had to ask for anything, he was on the ball. And all our food was out very quickly. There were some minor ambiance things that were a little off like the floor shaking when one of the buff servers walked through, but I realize not much can be done given the space and building restrictions.  I'm not sure why they're known for tots, though. The dipping sauce is good, but serving multiple sauces would be a better sell, to me, for otherwise regular tots. We got a coconut shrimp vermicelli bowl and the chicken curry rice bowl. I preferred the curry of the two, as I found the coconut shrimp bowl was lacking in something. We also ordered a Godzilla roll which was good (shoulda gone with our servers suggestion of drawn and buttered, though).  I recall stumbling in here a few months back late at night and having the dumplings - I'm definitely sorry I didn't get them this time around!

I was really excited to visit this place, friends have been telling me good things about it.  When I arrived at Sticky Rice, I opened the door. As I was about to walk in, someone in the street randomly approached me and said something. A few moments later, the host from inside the restaurant comes to the door and says somewhat annoyed, "Are you coming in?"  The food: Tots were terrific - well fried tots never ever fail. The Mongolian Beef, however, was disappointing. I was hoping for garlicky and a tad sweet. What was served were soggy vegetables and dry beef tossed with soy sauce and chili flakes. Gosh even my Coca-Cola was bland, as if the syrup was running low. I'm guessing the casual presentation of the food is meant to match the casualness of the ambience?  Ambience is very casual. Servers wear whatever they like. Lighting is dim, music is medium loud and the playlist is whatever, the place has an old look with some art and stickers on the walls. The crowd tonight was a noisy bunch. Sticky Rice seems like a fine place to sit down and have drinks and small bites with friends, but certainly not a place to impress a date.  Service was casual as well. It seemed that there was one server for the entire upper floor, and she had to go downstairs to pick up food and drinks.
Karaoke karaoke karaoke always fantastic here if and the food is muah!!!

Love the food: tater tots, sushi, noodles are all great. Unfortunately the service stinks. Servers are slow and inattentive. It doesn't matter if you are the only table upstairs, you will only see a server when they are bringing you something. Don't tell them you need another minute, because that will be 10-20.

Food was really good, especially the chicken lettuce wraps! Yummos! The teriyaki wings, sesame chicken all were great choices. Lychee Tini was ok, a bit strong but most folks like strong drinks. I would definitely recommend this place and will go again soon!
Check out the rain special.

So overall, this is a nice cozy place to chill and hangout. It appeared to be trendy and my bartender was helpful as he could be. Although I did not like the food at all I don't like scallions on all my food I'm sure others will. This place do have handicapped restroom enabled.  Many floors as well as a vegan menu as well. Sticky Rice has a great vibe. The food was very tasty, however with the exception of the bucket-of-tots the portions were VERY small. The bowls are not cheap and considering the size you get, I'd pause before coming again.

Natto temaki - Vegan/ vegetarian sushi has hit the District and Sticky Rice does it well! This location has been here for over 10 years and I finally decided to stop by. My friend and I ordered the veggie pot stickers, monster island: which consists of 3 rolls snap crackly pop, Godzirra drawn and buttered. Then 2 orders of the Santa Fe rolls.  Never would I think pot stickers without meat would be tasty, but this place makes it really yummy. The drawn and buttered had a nice creamy butter to compliment the tempura in the roll. Interesting concept better excecution. The Santa Fe is a must try. The combination of the agave with jalapeno and sweet potatoes created some nice textures.  Overall, I was really pleased with the service and quality of rolls. They have a great selection of cocktails and drinks for happy hour. I'll definitely be back to try their traditional rolls.

Used to like Sticky Rice but it seems as though the quality is getting lower and lower - recently visited and sat at the bar. It wasn't a busy night and the bartender was SUPER inattentive and apathetic about everything. Ordered a spicy margarita-like drink on the menu and I am not exaggerating when I say it was foul. Tasted like chemicals and when I asked what he'd put in it, he listed off the ingredients and walked away. Didn't ask why I was inquiring, or why I'd only taken a sip. It was awkward. Then I ordered a specialty spicy roll, only to realize after a few bites that it wasn't spicy at all and wasn't the right roll. The other bartender on duty felt bad and was kind about it, but our bartender/server didn't end up explaining what happened. Just walked over with our check and said he'd taken off 50% for the roll. Not oh sorry, I inputed it wrong or that the kitchen had made a mistake. Anyways, the drink was terrible and the food that night was sub-par at best but what will keep me away was the lack of good customer service. TONS of good spots on H and I'd rather go elsewhere at this point.
